      {
        "id": "3677966ea10793fbab165fa602d5587f49c0273a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 131,
          "name": "Mandeep Khinda",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "Mandeep.Khinda@gmail.com",
          "username": "mkhinda"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-12 13:46:22.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 15:\n\n@Venkata I looked into this briefly, and it seems to be because the chart is not defining an explicit pvc.yaml object and the SS is making a direct claim against the PV using \"volumeClaimTemplates:\".  When the chart is purged, helm doesn't have the knowledge of the claims made dynamically from the SS so it leaves them behind stuck in a \"Terminating\" state. The same problem exists in SDNC, APPC and possibly DCAE redis (also cases where there is only a PV object and no PVC object in the chart).  I can raise bugs for them all with details.",
        "patchset_number": 15
      }
    ]
